    pearls: ["Asking about suicide does NOT increase risk — this is the most important myth to dispel; direct, compassionate inquiry actually provides relief to patients and opens the door for intervention","Environmental safety is the NURSE'S PRIMARY domain — checking and modifying the room environment does not require a physician order; act immediately upon identifying risk","The first WEEK after psychiatric discharge is the HIGHEST-RISK period for completed suicide — caring contacts (phone call, text) within 24-72 hours of discharge reduce this risk","Hopelessness is a STRONGER predictor of suicide than depression severity — a patient with moderate depression but extreme hopelessness may be at higher risk than a patient with severe depression but retained hope","Sudden calmness after a period of agitation or depression may indicate the patient has MADE THE DECISION to act — this 'pseudo-improvement' should increase, not decrease, the nurse's vigilance","The Safety Planning Intervention (6-step Stanley-Brown plan) reduces suicide attempts by 50% — it takes 20-30 minutes and is a NURSING intervention that saves lives","Substance intoxication + suicidal ideation = EXTREME DANGER — intoxication dramatically increases impulsivity and reduces inhibition against self-harm; never discharge an intoxicated patient with suicidal ideation"],
